# Printonet Provisioning API Contract

## Endpoint

- `POST /wp-json/printonet/v1/provision-store`
- `POST /wp-json/printonet/v1/delete-store`
- `POST /wp-json/printonet/v1/slug-availability`
- `POST /wp-json/printonet/v1/tenant/config`
- `POST /wp-json/printonet/v1/tenant/pull-sync`
- `GET /wp-json/printonet/v1/tenant/pull-sync-status`
- `POST /wp-json/printonet/v1/suppliers/sync`
- `POST /wp-json/printonet/v1/suppliers/validate`
- `GET /wp-json/printonet/v1/suppliers/sync-status/{job_id}`
- `POST /wp-json/printonet/v1/suppliers/webhook`

## Authentication

- Preferred signed request headers:
  - `X-Printonet-Timestamp: <unix_epoch_seconds>`
  - `X-Printonet-Signature: <hex_hmac_sha256(timestamp + "." + raw_body, PLATFORM_HMAC_SECRET)>`
- Optional legacy fallback (only if `PRINTONET_ALLOW_LEGACY_API_KEY=true`):
  - `X-Printonet-Api-Key: <PROVISIONING_API_KEY>`

Replay protection:

- A valid signature can only be used once for the same method/route/timestamp/signature tuple.
- Reuse inside the 5-minute window is rejected.

## Request body

```json
{
  "tenant_slug": "acme-print",
  "request_id": "optional-idempotency-key-123",
  "store_name": "Acme Print",
  "admin_email": "owner@acmeprint.com",
  "admin_username": "acme_owner",
  "admin_password": "optional-strong-password",
  "primary_color": "#0f172a",
  "secondary_color": "#f8fafc",
  "logo_url": "https://cdn.printonet.com/logos/acme.png",
  "favicon_url": "https://cdn.printonet.com/favicons/acme.png",
  "currency": "USD",
  "default_country": "US:CA",
  "weight_unit": "lbs",
  "dimension_unit": "in"
}
```

If **`favicon_url`** is omitted, the engine installs the bundled network favicon from **`wp-content/mu-plugins/printonet-core/assets/favicon.ico`** as the WordPress site icon. Provide **`favicon_url`** to override per store.

Slug policy:

- lowercase letters, numbers, hyphens only
- max length: 40
- reserved slugs blocked (`www`, `admin`, `api`, `support`, `stores`, etc.)

## Delete store request

`POST /wp-json/printonet/v1/delete-store` â€” permanently deletes the tenant subsite (database tables dropped). Same HMAC signing as `provision-store`.

```json
{
  "tenant_slug": "acme-print",
  "request_id": "optional-idempotency-key-for-delete"
}
```

Responses:

- **200** â€” `{ "success": true, "site_id": 12, "tenant_slug": "acme-print" }` after deletion.
- **200** â€” `{ "success": true, "already_deleted": true, "tenant_slug": "acme-print" }` if that tenant site no longer exists (safe to treat as success when the dashboard retries).
- **200** â€” `{ "success": true, "idempotent": true, ... }` if `request_id` was already used for a successful delete.
- **403** â€” attempt to delete the main network site (never allowed).
- **422** â€” missing `tenant_slug` or invalid slug format.

