## Tenant config update request

Use this to push dashboard-driven config to each tenant store.

**Targeting:** Either send the request to the tenant origin (e.g. `https://greatprints.stores.printonet.com/...`) **or** send it to the **network base** (`https://stores.printonet.com/...`) and include **`tenant_slug`** in the JSON body (same signing rules). Do not send a `tenant_slug` that disagrees with the request hostname when calling a tenant URL.

```json
{
  "tenant_slug": "greatprints",
  "config_version": 12,
  "pull_sync_interval_minutes": 15,
  "status": "active",
  "branding": {
    "store_name": "Great Prints",
    "logo_url": "https://cdn.printonet.com/logos/greatprints.png",
    "favicon_url": "https://cdn.printonet.com/favicons/greatprints.png",
    "primary_color": "#0f172a",
    "secondary_color": "#f8fafc",
    "font_family": "Inter, sans-serif"
  },
  "woocommerce": {
    "currency": "USD",
    "default_country": "US:CA",
    "weight_unit": "lbs",
    "dimension_unit": "in"
  },
  "layout": {
    "hero_style": "split"
  },
  "homepage_sections": [
    { "id": "hero", "enabled": true },
    { "id": "featured_products", "enabled": true }
  ]
}
```

`status` values:

- `active` â€” storefront open for purchases (guest policy unchanged).
- `paused` â€” alias for **`suspended`** (checkout/purchasing blocked for guests; same behavior as suspended).
- `suspended` â€” checkout/purchasing blocked.

Include **`woocommerce`** only when updating currency, country, or units (same fields as `provision-store`).

## Tenant config read response

`GET /wp-json/printonet/v1/tenant/config`

Optional query when calling the network base: **`?tenant_slug=greatprints`**. Same hostname rule as POST: if you call a tenant host, `tenant_slug` must match.

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "tenant_slug": "greatprints",
  "status": "active",
  "branding": {
    "store_name": "Great Prints",
    "logo_url": "https://cdn.printonet.com/logos/greatprints.png",
    "favicon_url": "https://cdn.printonet.com/favicons/greatprints.png",
    "primary_color": "#0f172a",
    "secondary_color": "#f8fafc",
    "font_family": "Inter, sans-serif"
  },
  "woocommerce": {
    "currency": "USD",
    "default_country": "US:CA",
    "weight_unit": "lbs",
    "dimension_unit": "in"
  },
  "layout": { "hero_style": "split" },
  "homepage_sections": [],
  "config_version": 12,
  "config_hash": "sha256-hash",
  "synced_at": "2026-04-29 17:00:00"
}
```

Versioning behavior:

- If update payload has `config_version` lower than current stored version, API returns `409` (stale update rejected).
- Optional `pull_sync_interval_minutes` controls tenant pull cadence (`5`, `15`, or `60`).

## Tenant pull sync (manual trigger)

`POST /wp-json/printonet/v1/tenant/pull-sync`

- Pulls latest config from `PRINTONET_DASHBOARD_CONFIG_FEED_URL` using signed GET:
  - query: `tenant_slug=<store_host>`
  - headers: `X-Printonet-Timestamp`, `X-Printonet-Signature` where signature is `HMAC_SHA256("${timestamp}.", PLATFORM_HMAC_SECRET)`
- Applies config using same validation/versioning path as `POST /tenant/config`.

When calling from the **network base URL**, send JSON **`{ "tenant_slug": "greatprints" }`** so the engine switches to that subsite before pulling (same host/slug rule as config).

## Tenant pull sync status

`GET /wp-json/printonet/v1/tenant/pull-sync-status`

Optional query from the network base: **`?tenant_slug=greatprints`** (same hostname rule as config GET).

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "tenant_slug": "greatprints",
  "last_pull_status": "success",
  "last_pull_at": "2026-04-29 17:30:00",
  "last_pull_error": "",
  "last_pull_source": "https://.../tenant-config-feed",
  "last_config_sync": "2026-04-29 17:30:00",
  "config_version": 13,
  "config_hash": "sha256-hash",
  "pull_sync_interval_minutes": 15,
  "pull_fail_count": 0,
  "circuit_open_until": 0,
  "circuit_alert": false
}
```

## Success response

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "site_id": 12,
  "admin_user_id": 56,
  "store_url": "https://acme-print.stores.printonet.local"
}
```

If `request_id` is reused, endpoint returns existing tenant info with:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "idempotent": true,
  "site_id": 12,
  "admin_user_id": 56,
  "store_url": "https://acme-print.stores.printonet.local"
}
```

## Error responses

- `401/403`: invalid API key
- `409`: tenant already exists
- `422`: missing required fields
- `500`: site creation failure

